data.title: titled demonstration cassette EP, 1982
data.meta_description: A self-titled demonstration cassette EP with four songs by the Washington, D.C. area punk project, Falsex. Bethesda, Maryland musician Geoff Turner (then known as Jeff Turner) recorded the project under several pseudonyms—"Wing," "Jon," and "Oscar"—as listed on the cassette's cover. Turner later performed as part of the influential D.C. punk bands Gray Matter and Three, as well as other bands like Senator Flux and New Wet Kojak. He was also one of the primary record producers in the Washington, D.C. punk scene in the 1990s.
